SUMMARY:Hiking Weekend on Bruce Trail near Owen Sound 
DESCRIPTION:Toronto Bruce Trail Club\nJoin us for three days of hiking on 
 what many consider the most rugged section of the Bruce Trail. Overnight l
 odging will be in the Best Western Inn On The Bay in Owen Sound. (https://
 bwowensound.com/).\nThis will be a challenging three days of hiking with s
 ome strenuous climbs and sometimes difficult footing over tree roots\, roc
 ks and crevasses. All fit\, experienced hikers comfortable walking on this
  type or terrain are welcome. For your safety and enjoyment as well as the
  group's\, before registering we strongly encourage you to join some of ou
 r day hikes on the Bruce Trail. This will give you a chance to get to know
  us and assess your abilities.\nWe will split the group and offer two leve
 ls of hikes each day. The moderate group will hike about 12 km each day. a
 nd the fast group 15 km or more. The specific trails will be determined cl
 oser to the date.\nAccommodation cost is $339.98 + HST + gratuities per ro
 om for two nights’ accommodation. This does not include breakfasts\, lun
 ches\, snacks or dinners. The hotel has blocked 27 rooms with two queen be
 ds\, and 13 rooms with one queen/king bed plus pull-out couch for our grou
 p. Make sure you reserve a room that meets your needs.\n**Coach fare** is 
 $170 for members\; $190.00 for non-members\; $100 for children\n**Registra
 tion instructions:**\nIf you wish to share accommodation\, please find a r
 oommate\, then book your hotel room\, and then book your seats on the coac
 h. To avoid problems make sure you and your roommate reserve your seats at
  the same time.\n\n1. Book your room online using the Best Western Inn on 
 the Bay's TBTC group link. (https://www.bestwestern.com/en_US/book/hotel-r
 ooms.66070.html?groupId=H67FZ7K6). Or book by phone by calling the Best We
 stern Inn On The Bay at 519-371-9200\; to ensure you get the group rate\, 
 tell them you are with the Toronto Bruce Trail Club. Only one booking per 
 room is possible. Make arrangements with your roommate to split the cost.\
 n2. To reserve your seat on the bus\, register here https://hikes.brucetra
 il.org/ecwd_calendar/toronto/\n\n**Cancellation policy:** While we are hop
 ing for sunshine\, the trip cannot be cancelled due to weather. Coach fare
  is non-refundable if cancellation is made less than 30 days in advance of
  the departure date. Refund for cancellation more than 30 days in advance 
 of the departure date will be considered only if a replacement person is f
 ound and will be subject to a 10% processing fee.\nOur coach will depart a
 t 7:30 AM on Friday May 1. We plan to be back in Toronto between 7 and 8 P
 M on Sunday May 3. Departure locations: 10 York Mills Rd and HWY 400 and M
 ajor Mackenzie Park and Ride.
